{"word":"ἀμφίστημι","slug":"ἀμφίστημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμφίστημι</b></el> <p/><i>to place round</i>; only used in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <el>ἀμφίσταμαι</el>, with <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> aor2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>ἀμφέστην</el>, epic 3rd <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <el>ἀμφέσταν</el>; <a href='S:syncopated'>syncop.</a> 3rd <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἀμφεστᾶσι</el> (for <el>ἀμφεστήκασι</el>):— <i>to stand around</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/>"}]}